# Use `bun` as the package manager

The project uses `bun` as the package manager, here is how we manage the dependencies:

- `bun i` - install dependencies.
- `bun add <package>` - add a new package.
- `bun remove <package>` - remove an installed package.
- `bun update <package>` - update a installed package.
- `bun add -D <package>` - install package as development dependency.
- `bun run <script>` - run a script from `package.json`.
- `bunx --bun <package>` - directly run a package fom `npm`.

Useful commands:

- `bun run dev` - start the development server.
- `bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <component>` - add a [shadcn component](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components).
- `bun run build` - test a production build.
- `bun run check` - run linting, typecheck, and tests.

Always use `bun`. Do not use `npm`, `npx`, `yarn`, `pnpm` or other package managers.
